learning_outcomes.en:
In the end of the course participant is able to:
-	Comprehend the use of terms and principles of the law of the sea;
-	Identify the legal framework applicable to various maritime zones and grasps their interconnections;
-	Solve practical legal issues concerning the international law of the sea;
-	Interpret the compatibility of domestic law with the international law of the sea;
-	Explain the connections between the international law of the sea and other fields of law, e.g. international environmental law and security law;
-	Orientate in the legal literature on the international law of the sea.

learning_outcomes.et:
Kursuse läbinud üliõpilane:
- teab rahvusvahelise mereõiguse põhimõisteid;
- mõistab merevööndite õiguslikke raamistikke ja loob nendevahelisi seoseid;
- oskab lahendada elulisi mereõiguslikke probleeme;
- teab võrrelda siseriiklikku ja rahvusvahelist mereõigust ning hinnata nendevahelist kooskõla;
- oskab leida ja seostada rahvusvahelise mereõiguse alast kirjandust.

independent_work.et:
*	Independent work with study materials;
*	Writing a paper;
*	Presentation of the paper.
Instructions for writing and presenting the paper are made available through Moodle.
*       The lectures and other teachings will partly take place online.
